column5: Thanks!  Those lakers are amazing, I don't know if anyone else knows this, but there are several lakes up here, usually very small,  where the main feed is crayfish.  This leads to a lake trout with meat almost as pink as speckled trout.  The taste of these fish is simply amazing.  I prefer it over pickerel.  Eaten fresh its UNBELIEVABLE.
We are going to have to start calling you "Captain Video!"  Keep 'em coming TJ...awesome to watch!!
Thanks... I'm slowly adding all my old footage to my youtube channel, lots there to watch as well.   http://www.youtube.com/ontariofishing
Heading out for some lakers this weekend, and seeing that vicious strike gets the adrenaline flowing
Sashimi fresh? Love the videos TJ. Really educational to watch how fish attack.
Pretty cool. Guess I can toss out all my flourocarbon....
Pretty cool to see that trout come back for seconds
that song! my ear are bleeding!   then again awesome video.
